diff --git a/docs/ANTIMALWARE_0.1.1.md b/docs/ANTIMALWARE_0.1.1.md
--- a/docs/ANTIMALWARE_0.1.1.md
+++ b/docs/ANTIMALWARE_0.1.1.md
@@ -74,6 +74,10 @@ A quarantine operation is accepted only when all of the following complete:
 
 The payload and sidecar paths are protected from ordinary write, append, rename, remove and copy-over operations.
 
+Quarantine object names encode the first 96 bits of the complete SHA-256 digest. The previous 48-bit prefix admitted practical birthday collisions at roughly `2^24` chosen payloads, allowing one quarantined object to occupy the destination of another. Ninety-six bits is the strongest prefix that still permits both the `.qtn` payload and `.qtn.meta` sidecar within the 48-byte ZenovFS1 path limit. A boot self-test proves that two digests sharing the former 48-bit prefix produce distinct paths.
+
+This naming hardening prevents collision-driven quarantine denial; it does not claim content-addressed storage against a full SHA-256 collision.
+
 Deleting quarantine state is an explicit trusted shell action. Restore is reserved for rollback if metadata or audit commit fails.
